The paper deals with learning image representations through modeling human visual attention, specifically in the context of ultrasound video frames. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for the task of predicting gaze on ultrasound video frames suggests that the paper may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also involves transfer learning and the evaluation of learned representations, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of ultrasound video frames suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
